evidence: The highest measured hardnesses were found for Co 33 W 07 Al 33 Nb 24 Cr 03 (1084 ± 37 HV)

The marked difference in hardness between the two alloys is very interesting, particularly given that the compositional make-ups of the dendritic phases are not that dissimilar. In both cases, there is a significant component of Nb and W. In the case of the softest alloy, Ta is also present. One possible explanation is that the high hardness of Co 33 W 07 Al 33 Nb 24 Cr 03 is attributable to the significant volume fraction of the Nb-W phase, which is solid solution strengthened.
